  {
    "id": "kp-5.2-01",
    "section": "5.2",
    "order": 1,
    "title": "Perimeter and Area of Polygons",
    "title_zh": "多边形的周长与面积",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "The perimeter is the total distance around the edge of a shape, while the area is the space inside.\n\n**Rectangles and Squares** have an area of $base \\times height$ ($A = bh$).\n\n**Triangles** have an area of $\\frac{1}{2} \\times base \\times vertical\\ height$ ($A = \\frac{1}{2}bh$). Ensure the height is perpendicular to the base.\n\n**Parallelograms** have an area of $base \\times vertical\\ height$ ($A = bh$).\n\n**Trapeziums** (or trapezoids) have an area of $\\frac{1}{2}(a+b)h$, where $a$ and $b$ are the lengths of the parallel sides and $h$ is the perpendicular distance between them.",
      "zh": "周长是图形边缘的总长度，而面积是图形内部的空间大小。\n\n**长方形与正方形** 的面积为 底 $\\times$ 高 ($A = bh$)。\n\n**三角形** 的面积为 $\\frac{1}{2} \\times$ 底 $\\times$ 垂直高度 ($A = \\frac{1}{2}bh$)。确保高度与底边垂直。\n\n**平行四边形** 的面积为 底 $\\times$ 垂直高度 ($A = bh$)。\n\n**梯形** 的面积为 $\\frac{1}{2}(a+b)h$，其中 $a$ 和 $b$ 是平行边的长度，$h$ 是它们之间的垂直距离。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-trapezium-area",
        "label": "Calculate the area of a trapezium",
        "label_zh": "计算梯形面积",
        "description": "Substitute the parallel sides and height into the formula $A = \\frac{1}{2}(a+b)h$.",
        "description_zh": "将平行边和高代入公式 $A = \\frac{1}{2}(a+b)h$ 进行计算。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-trapezium-area",
        "question": "A trapezium has parallel sides of length $6\\,cm$ and $10\\,cm$. The perpendicular height is $5\\,cm$. Calculate its area.",
        "question_zh": "一个梯形的平行边长分别为 $6\\,cm$ 和 $10\\,cm$，垂直高度为 $5\\,cm$。计算其面积。",
        "solution": "**Step 1:** Identify the variables: $a = 6$, $b = 10$, $h = 5$.\n\n**Step 2:** Use the formula $A = \\frac{1}{2}(a+b)h$.\n\n**Step 3:** Calculate: $A = \\frac{1}{2}(6 + 10) \\times 5 = \\frac{1}{2}(16) \\times 5 = 8 \\times 5 = 40\\,cm^2$.\n\n**Answer:** $40\\,cm^2$",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：** 确定变量：$a = 6$，$b = 10$，$h = 5$。\n\n**步骤2：** 使用公式 $A = \\frac{1}{2}(a+b)h$。\n\n**步骤3：** 计算：$A = \\frac{1}{2}(6 + 10) \\times 5 = \\frac{1}{2}(16) \\times 5 = 8 \\times 5 = 40\\,cm^2$。\n\n**答案：** $40\\,cm^2$",
        "source": "0580/22/F/M/18"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
        "q": "The area of a triangle is $24\\,cm^2$ and its base is $8\\,cm$. What is its vertical height?",
        "q_zh": "一个三角形的面积为 $24\\,cm^2$，底边为 $8\\,cm$。它的垂直高度是多少？",
        "o": [
          "3 cm",
          "6 cm",
          "12 cm",
          "16 cm"
        ],
        "a": 1,
        "e": "$A = \\frac{1}{2}bh \\Rightarrow 24 = \\frac{1}{2} \\times 8 \\times h \\Rightarrow 24 = 4h \\Rightarrow h = 6\\,cm$.",
        "e_zh": "$A = \\frac{1}{2}bh \\Rightarrow 24 = \\frac{1}{2} \\times 8 \\times h \\Rightarrow 24 = 4h \\Rightarrow h = 6\\,cm$。"
      }
    ],
    "vocabLinks": [
      "polygons-area"
    ],
    "tier": "both"
  },
  {
    "id": "kp-5.3-01",
    "section": "5.3",
    "order": 1,
    "title": "Circles: Circumference and Area",
    "title_zh": "圆：周长与面积",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "Circles are defined by their radius ($r$) or diameter ($d = 2r$).\n\n**Circumference** ($C$) is the perimeter of a circle. The formula is $C = 2\\pi r$ or $C = \\pi d$.\n\n**Area** ($A$) of a circle is calculated using $A = \\pi r^2$. Always ensure you are using the radius, not the diameter, in this formula.\n\n**Semi-circles** and **Quarter-circles** have areas and curved perimeters that are fractions of a full circle ($\\frac{1}{2}$ and $\\frac{1}{4}$ respectively). Remember to add the straight edges (diameters or radii) if calculating the total perimeter.",
      "zh": "圆由半径 ($r$) 或直径 ($d = 2r$) 定义。\n\n**周长** ($C$) 是圆的边缘长度。公式为 $C = 2\\pi r$ 或 $C = \\pi d$。\n\n**面积** ($A$) 的计算公式为 $A = \\pi r^2$。计算面积时请务必确认使用的是半径而非直径。\n\n**半圆** 和 **四分之一圆** 的面积及弧长分别是全圆的 $\\frac{1}{2}$ 和 $\\frac{1}{4}$。在计算总周长时，切记加上直边（直径或半径）的长度。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-circle-calc",
        "label": "Basic area and circumference calculation",
        "label_zh": "基础面积与周长计算",
        "description": "Calculate $A$ or $C$ given $r$ or $d$, often leaving the answer in terms of $\\pi$ or to 3 significant figures.",
        "description_zh": "给定 $r$ 或 $d$，计算 $A$ 或 $C$。结果通常保留 $\\pi$ 或保留 3 位有效数字。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-circle-calc",
        "question": "A circle has a diameter of $14\\,cm$. Calculate its area, taking $\\pi = \\frac{22}{7}$.",
        "question_zh": "一个圆的直径为 $14\\,cm$。取 $\\pi = \\frac{22}{7}$，计算其面积。",
        "solution": "**Step 1:** Find the radius: $r = d \\div 2 = 14 \\div 2 = 7\\,cm$.\n\n**Step 2:** Use the area formula: $A = \\pi r^2$.\n\n**Step 3:** Calculate: $A = \\frac{22}{7} \\times 7^2 = \\frac{22}{7} \\times 49 = 22 \\times 7 = 154\\,cm^2$.\n\n**Answer:** $154\\,cm^2$",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：** 求半径：$r = d \\div 2 = 14 \\div 2 = 7\\,cm$。\n\n**步骤2：** 使用面积公式：$A = \\pi r^2$。\n\n**步骤3：** 计算：$A = \\frac{22}{7} \\times 7^2 = \\frac{22}{7} \\times 49 = 22 \\times 7 = 154\\,cm^2$。\n\n**答案：** $154\\,cm^2$",
        "source": "Adapted from 0580/11/O/N/19"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
        "q": "What is the circumference of a circle with radius $5\\,cm$? (to 1 decimal place)",
        "q_zh": "半径为 $5\\,cm$ 的圆周长是多少？（保留一位小数）",
        "o": [
          "15.7 cm",
          "31.4 cm",
          "78.5 cm",
          "10.0 cm"
        ],
        "a": 1,
        "e": "$C = 2\\pi r = 2 \\times \\pi \\times 5 = 10\\pi \\approx 31.4159\\,cm$.",
        "e_zh": "$C = 2\\pi r = 2 \\times \\pi \\times 5 = 10\\pi \\approx 31.4159\\,cm$。"
      }
    ],
    "vocabLinks": [
      "circle-parts"
    ],
    "tier": "both"
  },
  {
    "id": "kp-5.3-02",
    "section": "5.3",
    "order": 2,
    "title": "Arcs and Sectors",
    "title_zh": "弧与扇形",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "An arc is a part of the circumference, and a sector is a part of the area (like a slice of pizza).\n\n**Arc length** ($l$) is calculated by the fraction of the angle at the center ($\\theta$) over $360^\\circ$: $l = \\frac{\\theta}{360} \\times 2\\pi r$.\n\n**Sector area** ($A$) is calculated similarly: $A = \\frac{\\theta}{360} \\times \\pi r^2$.\n\n**Perimeter of a sector** is the sum of the arc length and the two radii: $P = l + 2r$. This is a common exam trap.",
      "zh": "弧是周长的一部分，而扇形是圆面积的一部分（类似于一片披萨）。\n\n**弧长** ($l$) 的计算方法是根据圆心角 ($\\theta$) 占 $360^\\circ$ 的比例：$l = \\frac{\\theta}{360} \\times 2\\pi r$。\n\n**扇形面积** ($A$) 的计算方法类似：$A = \\frac{\\theta}{360} \\times \\pi r^2$。\n\n**扇形的周长** 是弧长与两条半径之和：$P = l + 2r$。这是考试中常见的陷阱。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-sector-reverse",
        "label": "Find the angle or radius from sector area/arc length",
        "label_zh": "由扇形面积/弧长求圆心角或半径",
        "description": "Rearrange the formula to solve for the unknown variable $\\theta$ or $r$.",
        "description_zh": "变形公式以求解未知变量 $\\theta$ 或 $r$。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-sector-reverse",
        "question": "A sector of a circle with radius $6\\,cm$ has an angle of $60^\\circ$. Calculate the area of the sector.",
        "question_zh": "一个半径为 $6\\,cm$ 的扇形，圆心角为 $60^\\circ$。计算该扇形的面积。",
        "solution": "**Step 1:** Use the sector area formula: $A = \\frac{\\theta}{360} \\times \\pi r^2$.\n\n**Step 2:** Substitute values: $A = \\frac{60}{360} \\times \\pi \\times 6^2 = \\frac{1}{6} \\times 36\\pi = 6\\pi$.\n\n**Step 3:** Calculate numerical value: $6 \\times 3.14159 \\approx 18.8\\,cm^2$ (to 3 s.f.).\n\n**Answer:** $18.8\\,cm^2$",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：** 使用扇形面积公式：$A = \\frac{\\theta}{360} \\times \\pi r^2$。\n\n**步骤2：** 代入数值：$A = \\frac{60}{360} \\times \\pi \\times 6^2 = \\frac{1}{6} \\times 36\\pi = 6\\pi$。\n\n**步骤3：** 计算数值：$6 \\times 3.14159 \\approx 18.8\\,cm^2$（保留 3 位有效数字）。\n\n**答案：** $18.8\\,cm^2$",
        "source": "0580/23/M/J/21"
      }
    ],
    "testYourself": [
      {
        "q": "Find the arc length of a sector with radius $9\\,cm$ and angle $40^\\circ$.",
        "q_zh": "计算一个半径为 $9\\,cm$、圆心角为 $40^\\circ$ 的扇形弧长。",
        "o": [
          "2.0 cm",
          "6.28 cm",
          "12.57 cm",
          "28.27 cm"
        ],
        "a": 1,
        "e": "$l = \\frac{40}{360} \\times 2 \\times \\pi \\times 9 = \\frac{1}{9} \\times 18\\pi = 2\\pi \\approx 6.28\\,cm$.",
        "e_zh": "$l = \\frac{40}{360} \\times 2 \\times \\pi \\times 9 = \\frac{1}{9} \\times 18\\pi = 2\\pi \\approx 6.28\\,cm$。"
      }
    ],
    "vocabLinks": [
      "arc-sector"
    ],
    "tier": "both"
