  {
    "id": "kp-5.4-02",
    "section": "5.4",
    "order": 2,
    "title": "Pyramids, Cones, and Spheres",
    "title_zh": "棱锥、圆锥与球体",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "These shapes are generally part of the Extended syllabus but basic pyramid volume may appear in Core.\n\n**Pyramids and Cones** follow the general volume formula: $V = \\frac{1}{3} \\times base\\ area \\times vertical\\ height$.\nFor a **Cone**: $V = \\frac{1}{3}\\pi r^2 h$. The curved surface area is $\\pi rl$, where $l$ is the slant height ($l = \\sqrt{r^2 + h^2}$).\n\n**Spheres** have volume $V = \\frac{4}{3}\\pi r^3$ and surface area $A = 4\\pi r^2$. These formulas are usually provided in the exam paper.",
      "zh": "这些图形通常出现在 Extended 教学大纲中，但基础的棱锥体积也可能出现在 Core 中。\n\n**棱锥与圆锥** 遵循通用的体积公式：$V = \\frac{1}{3} \\times 底面积 \\times 垂直高度$。\n**圆锥**：$V = \\frac{1}{3}\\pi r^2 h$。其侧面积为 $\\pi rl$，其中 $l$ 是母线长度（$l = \\sqrt{r^2 + h^2}$）。\n\n**球体** 的体积 $V = \\frac{4}{3}\\pi r^3$，表面积 $A = 4\\pi r^2$。考试卷中通常会提供这些公式。"
    },
    "examPatterns": [
      {
        "id": "ep-sphere-calc",
        "label": "Volume and surface area of spheres",
        "label_zh": "球体体积与表面积",
        "description": "Apply the formulas $V = \\frac{4}{3}\\pi r^3$ and $A = 4\\pi r^2$ accurately.",
        "description_zh": "准确应用公式 $V = \\frac{4}{3}\\pi r^3$ 和 $A = 4\\pi r^2$。"
      }
    ],
    "examples": [
      {
        "patternId": "ep-sphere-calc",
        "question": "A sphere has a radius of $3\\,cm$. Find its volume in terms of $\\pi$.",
        "question_zh": "一个球体的半径为 $3\\,cm$。请用 $\\pi$ 表示其体积。",
        "solution": "**Step 1:** Use $V = \\frac{4}{3}\\pi r^3$.\n\n**Step 2:** Substitute $r = 3$: $V = \\frac{4}{3} \\times \\pi \\times 3^3$.\n\n**Step 3:** Calculate: $V = \\frac{4}{3} \\times \\pi \\times 27 = 4 \\times 9\\pi = 36\\pi$.\n\n**Answer:** $36\\pi\\,cm^3$",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：** 使用 $V = \\frac{4}{3}\\pi r^3$。\n\n**步骤2：** 代入 $r = 3$：$V = \\frac{4}{3} \\times \\pi \\times 3^3$。\n\n**步骤3：** 计算：$V = \\frac{4}{3} \\times \\pi \\times 27 = 4 \\times 9\\pi = 36\\pi$。\n\n**答案：** $36\\pi\\,cm^3$",
        "source": "0580/22/M/J/19"
      }
