    "title": "Compound Shapes",
    "title_zh": "组合图形",
    "explanation": {
      "en": "Compound (or composite) shapes are made by joining two or more simple shapes together.\n\n**Addition Strategy:** Break the shape into simpler rectangles, triangles, or circles. Calculate the area of each and add them together.\n\n**Subtraction Strategy:** Calculate the area of a large enclosing shape and subtract the area of any 'missing' parts or holes (e.g., a shaded region problem).\n\nFor 3D shapes, the same logic applies to volume. The total volume is the sum of the volumes of the component parts (e.g., a hemisphere on top of a cylinder).",
      "zh": "组合图形是由两个或多个简单图形拼接而成的。\n\n**相加策略**：将图形分解为简单的长方形、三角形或圆。分别计算每个图形的面积，然后相加。\n\n**相减策略**：计算一个较大的外部图形面积，然后减去“缺失”部分或孔洞的面积（常见于阴影面积题）。\n\n对于三维图形，体积计算逻辑相同。总体积等于各组成部分体积之和（例如，圆柱体上方放一个半球）。"
    },
