        "patternId": "ep-shaded-area",
        "question": "A square has side length $10\\,cm$. A circle with diameter $8\\,cm$ is cut out from its center. Calculate the remaining area.",
        "question_zh": "一个正方形边长为 $10\\,cm$。从中心切掉一个直径为 $8\\,cm$ 的圆。计算剩余面积。",
        "solution": "**Step 1:** Area of square = $side^2 = 10 \\times 10 = 100\\,cm^2$.\n\n**Step 2:** Radius of circle = $8 \\div 2 = 4\\,cm$. Area of circle = $\\pi \\times 4^2 = 16\\pi \\approx 50.27\\,cm^2$.\n\n**Step 3:** Remaining area = $100 - 50.27 = 49.73\\,cm^2$.\n\n**Answer:** $49.7\\,cm^2$ (to 3 s.f.)",
        "solution_zh": "**步骤1：** 正方形面积 = $边长^2 = 10 \\times 10 = 100\\,cm^2$。\n\n**步骤2：** 圆的半径 = $8 \\div 2 = 4\\,cm$。圆的面积 = $\\pi \\times 4^2 = 16\\pi \\approx 50.27\\,cm^2$。\n\n**步骤3：** 剩余面积 = $100 - 50.27 = 49.73\\,cm^2$。\n\n**答案：** $49.7\\,cm^2$（保留 3 位有效数字）",
